From 127ed492ad2df0aa2351a1ad32a793ae7d91161b Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Lijo Lazar <lijo.lazar@amd.com>
Date: Mon, 30 Jun 2025 19:11:33 +0530
Subject: drm/amdgpu: Pass adev pointer to functions
Git-commit: 127ed492ad2df0aa2351a1ad32a793ae7d91161b
Patch-mainline: v6.17-rc1
References: jsc#PED-13979 jsc#PED-14039 jsc#PED-14046 jsc#PED-14211 jsc#PED-14333 jsc#PED-14487 jsc#PED-14488 jsc#PED-14497 jsc#PED-14499 jsc#PED-15868

Pass amdgpu device context instead of drm device context to some
amdgpu_device_* functions. DRM device context is not required in those
functions. No functional change.

Signed-off-by: Lijo Lazar <lijo.lazar@amd.com>
Reviewed-by: Alex Deucher <alexander.deucher@amd.com>
Signed-off-by: Alex Deucher <alexander.deucher@amd.com>
Acked-by: Patrik Jakobsson <pjakobsson@suse.de>

